# Blog publishing workflow

## Source of truth

- **Author in** `sources/*.md` only. Files whose names start with `_` (e.g. `_TEMPLATE.md`) are skipped by the build.
- **Do not hand-edit** `blog/*.html` for content changes — they are generated.

## Markdown format (required)

1. **Line 1:** `# Title`
2. **Line 2:** blank
3. **Line 3:** byline exactly in this shape (date is parsed for sorting and the post header):

   `*By [Nick Raushenbush](https://www.nickraushenbush.com) — Mon D, YYYY*`

   Examples: `Jan 9, 2026`, `Mar 2, 2023`

4. **Line 4:** blank
5. **Body:** normal Markdown — `##` / `###`, paragraphs, `-` / `*` lists, `1.` lists, `> ` blockquotes, `---` separators, `**bold**`, `*italic*`, `[text](url)`.

## New post from rough notes

When the user pastes notes or asks to add a post:

1. Choose a **URL slug** (lowercase, hyphens): e.g. `my-topic-here` → file `sources/my-topic-here.md`.
2. Normalize their text into the **required layout** above; set title and date.
3. Run **`ruby scripts/build_posts.rb`** from the repo root (regenerates `blog/<slug>.html` and updates the **Thoughts** list in `index.html` between `<!-- POST_LIST_START -->` and `<!-- POST_LIST_END -->`).
4. Tell them to **commit and push** to deploy GitHub Pages (`git add -A && git commit -m "Add post: …" && git push`).

## Supported Markdown (build script)

The Ruby builder handles a focused subset (not full CommonMark). Prefer: headings `##`/`###`, paragraphs, lists, blockquotes, horizontal rules `---`, inline bold/italic/links. Avoid exotic syntax unless extending `scripts/build_posts.rb`.
